you cannout access a const of a base class from "outside" the class:

```
class base:
   const MY_CONST = 1


class child:
   extends base
   func _init():
      print("Test1: " + str(MY_CONST))


func _ready():
   var base_instance = base.new()
   var child_instance = child.new()
   print("Test2: " + str(base_instance.MY_CONST))
   print("Test3: " + str(child_instance.MY_CONST)) # will throw the error: Invalid get index 'MY_CONST'
```

if you make MY_CONST a var it works. but not with const.
